data.title: George Bernard Shaw's Birthplace
data.meta_description: This little home on Synge Street was the spot where G.B. Shaw came into the world.  It's a somewhat creepy view of Victorian life in that it's set up to seem as if the Shaw family just stepped out for the evening and you're walking through their house.  We got to the museum just in time.  They close for the winter on October 1st.
